<h3>Hackage</h3>

<p>
A <a href="http://www.haskell.org/cabal/">Cabal</a> package is available on <a href="http://hackage.haskell.org/cgi-bin/hackage-scripts/package/language-python">Hackage</a>.
</p>

<h2>Requirements</h2>

<ul>
<li>The <a href="http://www.haskell.org/ghc/">GHC</a> Haskell compiler version 6.10 and above. It may work with earlier versions of GHC too, but it has not been heavily tested with anything before the 6.10 series.

<li>The <a href="http://www.haskell.org/happy/">happy</a> parser generator version 1.17 or above.</li>

<li>The <a href="http://www.haskell.org/alex/">alex</a> lexer generator version 2.2 or above.</li>

<li>The <a href="http://www.haskell.org/haddock/">Haddock</a> document generator (if you want the API docs).</li>
</ul>

<h2>Installation</h2>

The best and easiest way to install the package is to use the Cabal infrastructure. See here for <a href="http://haskell.org/haskellwiki/Cabal/How_to_install_a_Cabal_package">instructions on how to install a Cabal package</a>. 

<h2>Reporting bugs, requesting features</h2>

<p>Preferred: add a Trac ticket via <a href="http://trac.haskell.org/language-python/report/1">trac-language-python</a>.</p>

<p>Less preferred: send an email to <a href="http://www.cs.mu.oz.au/~bjpop/">Bernie Pope</a>.</p>


